node.text:
YAY or NAY? Pineapple Ginger Juice 🍍
Follow @health_challlenge
Credit: @alphafoodie 
-
I love this sweet, refreshing, spicy, tangy, and tart juice. I sometimes enjoy it as shots and sometimes, I sip on the pineapple-ginger juice throughout the day. 🍹

All the details are on my blog. I also show how to make it with and without a juicer. Check this link:
https://www.alphafoodie.com/pineapple-ginger-juice-with-or-without-juicer/

Do you like pineapple juice?

Throwback to this Refreshing and delicious salad made of bell pepper, chickpeas, tomatoes , onion, parsley, coriander and lemon juice . it’s easy and quick to make and so tasty with lots of coriander, parsley and lime juice . Perfect for summer! .
💚😋 Ingredients :
1 bell pepper 
10 -15 cherry tomatoes 
1 can Chickpea 
1/2-1 red onion 
Parsley
Coriander 
Lime juice 
Salt pepper .

📸 Photo & Recipe: @jadoresmoothies (all this goodness and more on her page) ❤️

node.text:
Whipped Feta

Salty feta, sweet honey, sour lemon, creamy mascarpone... need I say more? This makes such a delicious starter or brunch dish with slow roasted tomatoes! 
-
by @londonbruncher

200g feta
4 heaped tbsp of mascarpone 
1/4 cup olive oil
1 tbsp honey
1/4 tsp dried oregano
Juice of 1/2-1 lemon
Zest of 1 lemon 
Salt and pepper

Put all of the ingredients in a food processor and blend until smooth.

I like to serve it with slow roasted tomatoes (recipe on my feed and reels)!

🚨 PSA: you don’t have to follow the food rules that society just made up out of thin air! 
Post by @nicolemarie_rd 

I know food rules can make you feel more in control around food, but ultimately they can lead to overeating, binging, and poor relationship with food and your body.

How do you know if it’s a food rule? Ask yourself a few questions:
👂where did you hear this from? If it wasn’t from a dietitian or physician, it’s likely diet culture 
❌Does demonize food or food groups? 
😖Does it make you feel guilty for eating specific food?
🥒Does it require you to eat “superfoods”?

If you answered yes to any of these, it’s likely a food rule with little to no evidence behind it. Ditch it and ask yourself what will make you feel good and satisfy you

BBQ Shrimp + Limey Avocado Salsa Meal Prep Bowls 🌞🔥🥑 
 
This combo is so darn tasty and SATISFYING...plus, it comes together FAST! So, make it for lunch or dinner this weekend, and be sure to double the recipe, then store the extra servings - so that your next few days are much simpler! }... 
 
makes 4 servings 
Ingredients:
2 pounds large shrimp, deveined and peeled
2 cups cherry tomatoes, cut into quarters
1 large avocado, pitted and chopped
4 green onions, chopped
2 fresh limes, juiced
1 handful fresh cilantro leaves, chopped
1 Tbsp avocado oil, or extra virgin olive oil
sea salt and freshly ground black pepper
lime wedges, to garnish

For serving:
2 cups cooked brown rice

for the BBQ spice mix:
1 Tbsp. smoked paprika
1 tsp ground cumin 
1/2 tsp cayenne powder
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/4 tsp sea salt, or to taste

Instructions:
In a large glass mixing bowl place shrimp and BBQ seasoning ingredients and gently stir well to combine. 
Set aside for just a few minutes.

In another bowl, add chopped tomatoes, avocado, onions, cilantro, lime juice, sea salt and pepper. Very gently toss to combine. 
Set aside.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add shrimp and cook for 1-2 minutes on each side or until they've turned pink and form a nice lightly charring in spots as pictured.

Add 1/2 cup cooked brown rice to each bowl or meal prep container.
Then divide the cooked shrimp and avocado salsa equally, and nicely among the 4 bowls, or meal prep containers as shown.
